12/12/2021, 14:36 - +91 84273 11044: All students who are admitted in B.E. first year (all courses) are required to email the scanned copy (in PDF format) of following documents till 13.12.2021 before 4.30 pm:
1.	10th Mark sheet/ Pass certificate 
2.	12th Mark sheet
3.	Migration or Transfer certificate (transfer Certificate should be counter signed by District Education officer (if you have migration certificate then no need to send Transfer certificate)
4.	Aadhar Card 
5.	No need to send transfer certificate if you have migration certificate 
6.	Those who have passed 12th from CBSE Board are not required to send migration or transfer certificate they have to send rest of the documents 
Above documents are mandatory to email for those who are studying in B.E. First year UIET Chandigarh
Email address is: appliedscienceuiet@gmail.com 
In the email, please mention the subject in CAPITAL LETTERS as NAME, ROLL NUMBER, BRANCH, DOCUMENTS 
Students please read this carefully

This group has been made to share all the important information for *IT Section-2* students.

All IT Students can join this group. If you are not from IT please don't join.

31/12/2021, 09:01 - +91 84273 11044: Encoding ka bhi farak pdta h
31/12/2021, 09:08 - +91 84273 11044: - *Auto-gen PDF*
In start it consists of a Form with empty blanks for you information. After you generate it, it is filled with your details in text format (not image) and that is saved as PDF. It is like typing the whole form on Word document and then saving it as PDF.

- *Scanner Apps*
They capture your image and embed into a PDF. It is like inserting an image in your Word document and saving it as PDF.

(Also, auto-generated PDF have sometimes virtual encrypted code, which is not visible on PDF Reader Apps. But it can be used to check authenticity of document.)
_I hope this doubt should be clear now_

09/01/2022, 13:28 - Trishan Preet Singh: Mistakes often  commited -
1) Vise/wise--- right word vice
2) filling--- right word filing.
3). Sq window 20x20 cutting operation---- first do marking of 20x20 window with vernier height gauge , then mark the  centre of 20x20 window with centre punch.
4) hold the job in machine vice and fit dia 19 mm drill bit in drill machine.
5). Do the 19 mm drill at centre of 20x20 pocket.
6). Then enlarge the dia 19 hole in square shape (i.e. 20x 20mm) with filing practice.


Correct all mispelled tools and operation names.
09/01/2022, 13:28 - Trishan Preet Singh: Tell all if any size of open square/ rectangular/ window is shown in drawing, then first do 1mm less dia drill at centre of that pocket and then do filing of cut hole in specified dimensions. It may be square or rectangular section.

11/01/2022, 22:37 - +91 84273 11044: *_DISCORD TUTORIAL_*
*MOM (Minutes of Meet) 11 Jan - 9PM*
   1. Intro to phone interface.
	- Swipe to see channels and members list
	- Types of channels (DM, Text, Voice)
	- Sending texts and connecting to voice
	- Using DMs (As simple as whatsapp)
	- Adding friends and user settings
   2. Intro to PC interface
	- No need to to swipe, but info is in one screen
	- Sending text, connecting to voice
	- Creating groups
	- Adding friends and User settings   
   3. How Discord is better than Whatsapp?
	- Using reactions for acknowledgments
	- Deleting messages for everyone after long time
	- Intro to Server (Collection of whatsapp groups)
	- No need for again & again inviting same people to different groups
	- No unwanted messages mixing with the important messages
	- In terms of limit > Whatsapp : Discord :: 256 : 6Lakhs
   4. Only IT Zone
	- If you are from IT, fill the form to get access. https://forms.gle/KGqEenFvu3V33NYc8
	- Join the Official IT server (Coder's Cafe) here https://dsc.gg/it-uiet
   5. Special features added by admins.
	- Update profile for avoiding confusion whether the person is a girl/boy
	- The first ever server of UIET to have it's own official API bot to provide info
	- Listen to Music
	- Get movie/TC show suggestions
   6. General doubts by everyone including common FAQs.
   7. The meeting ended on a good note with everyone now knowing about discord.

Thanks for everyone who joined the meet. If you still have any doubt you can ask and get help. 
And for those who couldn't join, Don't worry!! We will have this again. Please decide a time and tell so that we arrange it accordingly. You can also ask any particular doubt if you want. 

Best Regards
Discord Admin

PD = |ax|Â² = aÂ²xÂ²
Since the particle is limited to x axis,

Probability =  
We need to find Probability for finding the particle between x = 0.45 and x  =0.55

P =   =    = aÂ² (0.55)Â³ - (0.45)Â³ /3
P = aÂ² x (0.166375 - 0.091125 )/3 = 0.0251aÂ²
Therefore the probability of finding a particle between x =0.45 and x=0.55 is 0.0251aÂ².

14/01/2022, 21:12 - +91 84273 11044: 1. Intro to phone interface.
	- Swipe to see channels and members list
	- Types of channels (DM, Text, Voice)
	- Sending texts and connecting to voice
	- Using DMs (As simple as whatsapp)
	- Adding friends and user settings
   2. Intro to PC interface
	- No need to to swipe, but info is in one screen
	- Sending text, connecting to voice
	- Creating groups
	- Adding friends and User settings   
   3. How Discord is better than Whatsapp?
	- Using reactions for acknowledgments
	- Deleting messages for everyone after long time
	- Intro to Server (Collection of whatsapp groups)
	- No need for again & again inviting same people to different groups
	- No unwanted messages mixing with the important messages
	- In terms of limit > Whatsapp : Discord :: 256 : 6Lakhs
   4. Only IT Zone
	- If you are from IT, fill the form to get access. https://forms.gle/KGqEenFvu3V33NYc8
	- Join the Official IT server (Coder's Cafe) here https://dsc.gg/it-uiet
   5. Special features added by admins.
	- Update profile for avoiding confusion whether the person is a girl/boy
	- The first ever server of UIET to have it's own official API bot to provide info
	- Listen to Music
	- Get movie/TC show suggestions
   6. General doubts by everyone including common FAQs.
   7. The meeting ended on a good note with everyone now knowing about discord.

14/01/2022, 23:37 - +91 84273 11044: *MOM (Minutes of Meet) 14 Jan - 9PM*
*Discord Tutorial & Minor Info*

   1. Intro to Discord
	- Phone interface v/s PC interface
	- Using channels for specific purposes
	- Perks of using discord over whatsapp
	- Using "Only IT Zone" for Minor discussion with proper rules
   2. Discussing everyone's doubts about using discord.
   3. Minor Info
	- Remember to divide the paper into into sections and start from different sections. So that when reaching the end, you have a complete paper with all answers combined all together. Then you can share the answers with each other.
	- Calculus should be done at medium pace. Try to score good enough marks. Minimize errors and reduce time wastage.
	- ITIT and PFPS are scoring subjects and improve the final grade. Not at all lengthy. Should contain maximum accuracy for full marks.
	- Quantum Physics will be lenghty and tough. Keep a good pace in th start. And remember not to solve any question, thinking that it is from JEE syllabuus because there won't be. And try to write at least one question on your own to get your paper completed on time.
	- Make your PDF proper with 8 pages. Every page should have Signature (top & bottom) and page no. on top right.
   4. Discussion for Minors
	- Who is comfortable with which subjects?
	- Which material to access for studying?
   5. The meeting officially ended on a good note with everyone now knowing about discord and with a little more knowledge of minors.

Wishing you all best of luck for Minor-1  ğŸ‘

Happy Studying

17/01/2022, 14:36 - +91 84273 11044: for ( i = 10 ; i ; i -- )
generally for loop aise use hota h initialise ; condition ; increment

but tu isko aise bhi likh skta hai...  for ( ; condition ; ) 
isme baaki dono part khali chhod diye hai

third thing is....  for ( any valid line ; condition ; any valid line ) would work normal
But those "any valid line" dont mean anything in ur program. Unke hone na hone se farak ni pdta unless they what they should be i.e., initialisation in first slot and increments in 3rd

The Psych Club is back with yet another insightful and educational session in collaboration with BPC UIET.ğŸ§ 

_*"The bravest thing I ever did was continuing my life when I wanted to die"*_
*_-Juliette Lewis_*

A lot of times we find ourselves in situations where we feel helpless and lost. We struggle to work, sleep, talk, or do anything in general. Life becomes very sad, dull and difficult. 
We all have our lows and often find it difficult to escape this Labyrinth and wish it could all just end. For every high in life there is a low and itâ€™s crucial that one knows how to tackle the lows.
But... Is that really the answer to our problems?

To address this topic, The Psych Club in collaboration with *The Connect Hut*  brings you a webinar on the topic : 

 *_"Is suicide something to be afraid of?"_*
*by Sachin Chitambaran* , Founder and Lead Trainer,
The Connect Hut. 

*Date : 11th February 2022*
*Time : 4:00 PM*
*Platform : WebEx*

To attend the webinar register using the link below: 
https://forms.gle/bGnHx3HC9FZDh6xU9

09/03/2022, 10:51 - +91 97218 30891: #include <stdio.h>
unsigned long factorial(unsigned short int);
float power(float, unsigned short int);

int main() {
    unsigned short n = 10, i = 0;
    float x, sum = 0;

    printf("Enter an angle to calculate its sine: ");
    scanf("%f", &x);

    while(i < n) {
        if(i%2 == 0)
            sum += power(x,2*i+1)/(float) factorial(2*i+1);
        else
            sum -= power(x,2*i+1)/(float) factorial(2*i+1);
        i++;
    }

    printf("Sum upto %hd terms = %f", n, sum);

    return 0;
}

float power(float x, unsigned short n) {
    float pow = 1;

    while(n > 0) {
        pow *= x;
        --n;
    }

    return pow;
}

unsigned long factorial(unsigned short n) {
    unsigned long f;

    if(n == 0 || n == 1)
        return 1;
    else
        f = n * factorial(n-1);

    return f;
}

The revised final list will be displayed tomorrow after 3 pm or on Monday morning till then please wait

22/04/2022, 13:45 - raghav: #include <stdio.h>
int main() {
    int n, i;
    float num[100], sum = 0.0, avg;

    printf("Enter the numbers of elements: ");
    scanf("%d", &n);

    while (n > 100 || n < 1) {
        printf("Error! number should in range of (1 to 100).\n");
        printf("Enter the number again: ");
        scanf("%d", &n);
    }

    for (i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
        printf("%d. Enter number: ", i + 1);
        scanf("%f", &num[i]);
        sum += num[i];
    }

    avg = sum / n;
    printf("Average = %.2f", avg);
    return 0;
}

01/09/2022, 10:06 - Trishan Preet Singh: #include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    int a,b=0,c;

    cout<<"Enter the numbers of elements in array: ";
    cin>>a;

    int arr[a];

    for(int i=0;i<a;i++){
        cout<<"Enter the "<<i+1<<" element of array: ";
        cin>>arr[i];
        b++;
    }

    int n;
    cout<<"Type the postion where you want to add element: ";
    cin>>n;

    for(int i=a+1;i>n;i--){
        arr[i]=arr[i-1];
    }

    cout<<"Type the number which you want to add: ";
    cin>>c;

    arr[n]=c;

    for(int i=0;i<=a;i++){
        cout<<arr[i]<<endl;
    }
    return 0;
}

using namespace std;

int main()
{

21/09/2022, 10:49 - +91 84273 11044: #include <iostream>
#include <queue>

using namespace std;

void showq(queue<int> gq)
{
	queue<int> g = gq;
	while (!g.empty()) {
		cout << '\t' << g.front();
		g.pop();
	}
	cout << '\n';
}

int main()
{
	queue<int> gquiz;
	gquiz.push(10);
	gquiz.push(20);
	gquiz.push(30);

	cout << "The queue gquiz is : ";
	showq(gquiz);

	cout << "\ngquiz.size() : " << gquiz.size();
	cout << "\ngquiz.front() : " << gquiz.front();
	cout << "\ngquiz.back() : " << gquiz.back();

	cout << "\ngquiz.pop() : ";
	gquiz.pop();
	showq(gquiz);

	return 0;
}

€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€ €‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹â€‹


I know that i am CR of the class and us cheez ki responsibility poori bhi krta hu. Par har baar har cheez ka blame mere upar daalna is not fair. Jab kaam ho to message kroge. Apni marzi karni ho to kar loge. Kuchh galat ho to mere pe blame krna hai. Baaki har cheeez mai me maa chudane chala jata hu.
CR hu, tumhara naukar nhi hu behen k lodo. Aur jis unity ki tum log baat krte ho ek mai bhi nhi h tumme se. Jab apna kaam nikalna hota hai to apni dekhte ho bas. To dusro se mat expect kro ki vo tumhari sunenge. Jab koi detain hota hai tumhare "BUNK" k karan tab teacher se milke ladne aao, vo hoti h unity. Jis bunk se unity dikhana chahte ho, ek ki bhi aukaat nhi hai tumhari. Tum bhi nhi sunoge kisiki jab khudpe baat aaegi.
.
So, I would suggest ab jab 4 sem selfish hoke nikale hai to ab sochne ka start mat kro and apna sochlo bas.

To end, as a CR jab help mangoge krunga and krta bhi hu. Jisko pata hona chahiye unka pata hai. Baaki apni maa chuda skte hai.

PEACE OUT !!

05/12/2023, 11:00 - Mayank: import re

def search_patterns(file_name, pattern):
    result = []
    with open(file_name, 'r') as file:
        for line in file:
            if re.search(pattern, line):
                result.append(line.strip())
    return result

file_name = 'VehicleFile.txt'
pattern_to_search = 'HR 26 \d{4}'  # \d{4} matches any four digits (0-9)
matches = search_patterns(file_name, pattern_to_search)

for match in matches:
    print(match)
